    "macroSummary": "Markets are in a binary risk-off state ahead of Trump's Iran deadline with oil above $110 triggering stagflation concerns and mixed economic data showing resilient capital goods orders but weaker overall durable goods. The dollar and gold are volatile as investors position defensively, while crypto sees selective flows into XRP despite Bitcoin sentiment deteriorating and major whale liquidations occurring.",
